# Competitive Analysis

## Google Tasks
Simple UI  
Limited categories and no color-coding  
Hard to prioritize tasks

## Todoist
Project-based organization  
Priority labels and filters  
Can feel overwhelming to new users

## Microsoft To Do
Nice UI  
Task steps are useful  
Too many clicks to do simple things

---

# Key Takeaways:
- Prioritization needs to be easier.
- Task entry should be fast.
- Simplicity is key â€” most people just want to *add, check off, and maybe schedule*.
